did.abstract: The collection is primarily concerned with the Society of Women Engineers- Houston Area Section, though it also contains material from the regional and national levels of the organization. Material in the collection includes correspondence, business and financial records, photographs, and publications of the organization. The collection is divided into eleven series: Correspondence, Financial Documents, Organizational Governance, Meeting Minutes, Society of Women Engineers Publications, Printed Materials, Society of Women Engineers Regional and National Conference Materials, Retreats and Workshops, National Materials and Programs, Audio-visual and Mixed Media, and Various. All series are arranged topically and chronologically.

bioghist.head: Historical Note:
bioghist.p: The Society of Women Engineers (SWE) was founded on May 27, 1950 at the Green Engineering Camp of the Cooper Union in New Jersey as a non-profit educational resource and support to help promote Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics for women. On October 14 of the same year, the National Board met under the first president of the SWE, Dr. Beatrice A. Hicks. The following year not only saw the first National Conference in New York City but also the first chapter in Pittsburgh. Sections were chartered in Chicago and Los Angeles soon after, as well as student sections at Drexel and Purdue universities. Over the last six decades the SWE has grown to include ten regional sections made up of numerous professional and student sections. The Houston Area section was chartered July 1, 1979 as the thirty-third section.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection is primarily concerned with the Society of Women Engineers- Houston Area Section, though it also contains material from the regional and national levels of the organization. Material in the collection includes correspondence, business and financial records, photographs, and publications of the organization. The collection is divided into eleven series: Correspondence, Financial Documents, Organizational Governance, Meeting Minutes, Society of Women Engineers Publications, Printed Materials, Society of Women Engineers Regional and National Conference Materials, Retreats and Workshops, National Materials and Programs, Audio-visual and Mixed Media, and Various. All series are arranged topically and chronologically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of correspondence of the Society of Women Engineers Houston Area and Texas Section. The material is organized chronologically consisting of the years 1972-2005. The correspondence focuses primarily on organizational and fundraising issues.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of financial documents of the Society of Women Engineers Houston Area. The series is comprised of receipts and financial documents, corporate sponsorship, and scholarships and awards. Both sub-series Financial Reports and Scholarships are arranged topically while the sub-series Industrial support is organized chronologically.

did.unittitle: IRS Forms and Various Financial Documents

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series is comprised of documents concerning the organizational governance of the Society of Women Engineers both locally and nationally. The first sub-series includes documents regarding board of trustees, bylaws of the SWE and officer ballots and is organized topically. The second sub-series contains membership lists and directories of the Houston Area section of the SWE and is arranged chronologically.

SWE Central New Mexico Section Board of Trustees Procedure

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of the meeting minutes of the SWE arranged chronologically from 1970-2009. The series revolves primarily around Houston Area section meetings but also includes Region C documents. Region C included the Houston Area Section of the SWE.

Executive Board Meeting, Section Representative Folder

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains publications distributed by the SWE both locally and nationally. The first sub-series contains SWE Houston Area publications, divided into two sets of newsletters that are each organized chronologically. Sub-series 2 and 3 contain the SWE national newsletter and Members at Large Newsletter. The final sub-series is comprised of the national organization magazine published under various monikers; the SWE Newsletter, U.S. Woman Engineer, and SWE.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of various materials printed by the Society of Women Engineers and other engineering organizations. The first two sub-series are organized chronologically and the last topically. The first sub-series consists primarily of SWE brochures and flyers and the following two sub-series contain articles regarding engineering and publications from various engineering organizations.

did.unittitle: Assorted Engineering Publications and Printed Materials
Society of Women Engineers Regional and National Conference Materials

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains materials regarding local, regional, and national Society of Women Engineer conferences as well as other local events. The first sub-series is comprised of materials from the SWE National Conference held in Houston in 1998, in which the local chapter of the SWE played an integral role. The last three sub-series focus on local, regional and national conferences that the Houston Area Section of the SWE participated. The series is comprised of correspondence, flyers and brochures, and photographs.

scopecontent.p: This series consists of materials from the Region C section of the Society of Women Engineers. The series includes “Vitality Retreat,” continuing and professional development programs materials. All sub-series are arranged chronologically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of printed materials, awards, and information disseminated by the Society of Women Engineers on a national level. The series includes information on rewards, charters, and career guidance programs. Each sub-series is organized chronologically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains various media items that revolve around the Society of Women Engineers. The series consists of photographs, VHS tapes, and computer CDs.
